---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<section>
	<h2>HeathBarSec</h2>

	<p>
		<strong>Cloud Security • Detection Engineering • AI • Incident Response</strong>
	</p>

	<p>
		Welcome to HeathBarSec.
	</p>

	<p>
		This blog is where I document practical blue team research, cloud detection engineering,
		and incident response techniques across AWS, Azure, GCP, and modern identity platforms.
	</p>

	<p>
		My goal is to break down real attack techniques into actionable detections,
		investigation workflows, and prevention strategies that security engineers and defenders
		can immediately apply. Along the way, I&apos;ll also explore AI-driven detection engineering,
		security tooling, and software projects that improve how defenders investigate and respond
		to threats.

	</p>

	<p>
		Whether it&apos;s cloud identity compromise, OAuth abuse, IAM persistence, or building
		AI-assisted security workflows, HeathBarSec is a place to share research, experiments,
		and lessons learned through hands-on security engineering.
	</p>

	<p>
		<a href="/blog/">Read the blog →</a>
	</p>
</section>
		</main>

		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
